<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" type="text/css">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Red+Hat+Mono&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <title>
        <%= title %>
    </title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Documentation</h1>
<p>
    This source serves for restAPI of images of anime girls which holding programming books. You can have more
    information at
    <a href="https://github.com/lokot0k/anime-girls-holding-programming-books-RESTapi">Github's repo</a>.<br> All of the
    requests must be done on <code>/api/</code> route
</p>
<h2>Response structure</h2>
<p>
    All of the GET methods return set of JSONs with following structure:
</p>
<pre>
<code>
{
    "id": number,
    "language": string,
    "url": string,
    "size": number
}
</code>
</pre>
<h2>Routes</h2>
<h3>GET</h3>
<ul>
    <li><code>/:language_name/</code> route returns an array of JSONs</li>
    <li><code>/:id/</code> route returns one JSON</li>
</ul>
<p>
    Server returns 404 status code if not any requested content found. <br/>
    <code>:language_name</code> parameter must be a string and <code>:id</code> parameter must be an integer
</p>
<h3>POST</h3>
<p>POST method must be done at /api/ route. Body of request should have JSON with following fields:</p>
<ul>
    <li>"name": string - name of picture with extension without spaces. Example:
        "Atsuko_Kagari_Holding_Introducing_Elixir.png"
    </li>
    <li>"language": string - name of programming language. If language has "#" in its name then you should write "sharp"
        instead.
        Example: "csharp"
    </li>
    <li>
        "url": string - url of picture. It will be downloaded to the server, so you can use a one-time url in this
        field.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>Headers of request should contain "Authorization" header with "Basic some_secret_key" like value. You can get it from
    a server owner.
    This was made because of safety and keep-db-clean reasons
</p>
</body>
</html>